## PART IV: THINGS THAT WILL GO WRONG — EXPLICIT LIST

| # | Failure Mode | Detection | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Stale regime forward-fill across gap** | p99 gap between consecutive same-regime trades > 5 min | Nullify regime where gap > threshold |
| 2 | **Duplicate BBO timestamps** | p50 inter-event time < 0.1ms | Group by ts_ms, keep last event |
| 3 | **Mid at EOD = NaN for all h horizons** | Check null % matches expected EOD truncation | Drop these rows from markout analysis only |
| 4 | **IMC/market split is regime-confounded** | Crosstab `imc_caused × regime` shows imbalance > 30pp | Stratify: only compare within (action, regime) |
| 5 | **Tick size detection wrong** | `OTHER` > 5%, or tick detected as 0.1 when true is 0.05 | Check exchange tick table; hardcode |
| 6 | **Crossed book corrupting mid** | `bid > ask` events > 0% | Drop crossed events before mid calculation |
| 7 | **Regime transitions at trade boundaries only** | Fast transitions > 5% | Switch from merge_asof to interval join |
| 8 | **Vol change = 0 every row** | BID_JOIN + ASK_JOIN + BID_CANCEL + ASK_CANCEL all near 0 | Check if `bid_vol` is snapshot (cumulative) not delta — needs `.diff()` |
| 9 | **Concentration in single time window** | Single minute > 50% of bucket | Flag; do not report the number |
| 10 | **Unit mismatch: bid_price in paise, mid in rupees** | Tick detected as 5.0 instead of 0.05 | Normalize all prices to same unit at ingestion |

